Consideration #1
When an outside component provides captivating functionality that we’d like to 
reuse, but it’s incompatible with our current application. A suitable Adapter can
 be developed to make them compatible with each other
 
Consideration #2
When our application is not compatible with the interface that our client is expecting

Consideration #3
When we want to reuse legacy code in our application without making any modification 
in the original code

Consideration #4
Adapter is used when you have an abstract interface, and you want to map that 
interface to another object which has similar functional role, but a different 
interface.